00:39:40.520 --> 00:39:41.990
It was before this--

00:39:41.990 --> 00:39:44.750
Bulova watch catalog.

00:39:44.750 --> 00:39:47.600
SPEAKER 2: Do you and your band
have time for one more song?

00:39:47.600 --> 00:39:48.475
DAVID DUCHOVNY: Yeah!

00:39:48.475 --> 00:39:49.330
SPEAKER 2: Cool.

00:39:49.330 --> 00:39:52.280
DAVID DUCHOVNY: You asked
if there was a song that

00:39:52.280 --> 00:39:53.390
was meaningful to me.

00:39:53.390 --> 00:39:58.010
So actually, the last song
that we're going to do also

00:39:58.010 --> 00:39:59.657
involves my father.

00:39:59.657 --> 00:40:01.490
It's called "Stranger
and the Sacred Heart."

00:40:01.490 --> 00:40:05.480
And we were touring in
Europe, and we were in Paris.

00:40:05.480 --> 00:40:08.150
And I went to this
church called The Sacred

00:40:08.150 --> 00:40:10.360
Heart, which is in the
neighborhood of the hotel I

00:40:10.360 --> 00:40:10.985
was staying at.

00:40:10.985 --> 00:40:18.710
And I was told by the
folks there that people--

00:40:18.710 --> 00:40:21.509
the custom there is
to pray for others,

00:40:21.509 --> 00:40:22.550
not to pray for yourself.

00:40:22.550 --> 00:40:27.260
And actually, to pray
for the world really,

00:40:27.260 --> 00:40:31.020
not just Paris, not just French
people, but actually the world.

00:40:31.020 --> 00:40:34.360
And I thought, I'd
never heard that before.

00:40:34.360 --> 00:40:35.280
And I really liked it.

00:40:35.280 --> 00:40:39.400
So the song, along with
the fact that my father had

00:40:39.400 --> 00:40:44.188
died in Paris a few years
earlier, kind of came together.

00:40:44.188 --> 00:40:49.396
It's called "Stranger
and the Sacred Heart."

